\section*{Broader Impacts}

This School aims to increase diversity and inclusion in the
applied category theory community and to build a stronger
relationship between academia and industry.

Regarding diversity and inclusion, the School will be
advertised to potential students through established
networks in the applied category theory community and also
though the National Association of Mathematicians, the
Association for Women in Mathematics, Spectra, the Society
for the Advancement of Chicanos and Native Americans in the
Sciences.  

A strong relationship between industry and academia exists
because of a consensus on the importance of this
relationship to the success of applied category theory.
Category theory informs work at various US companies and
government agencies. By selecting representatives from
industry and academia as our project leads and students, the
relationship will be further strengthened. 

